Former Virginia Gov . 
  Bob McDonnell was sentenced to two years in prison for selling the influence of his office to the CEO of a dietary supplements company . 
  He and his wife Maureen McDonnell were convicted of accepting $165,000 in gifts and loans in exchange for promoting the company . 
  McDonnell is appealing his conviction to the 4th Circuit Court of Appeals . 
  He argues that the favors he did for the businessman were routine courtesies and not part of a bribery scheme . 
  The former governor made the argument in a 54-page brief to the appeals court . 
  McDonnell was convicted of public corruption in September . 
 